    "description": [
        {
            "text": "Coulomb Per Cubic Meter ($C/m^{3}$) is a unit in the category of Electric charge density. It is also known as coulomb per cubic metre, coulombs per cubic meter, coulombs per cubic metre, coulomb/cubic meter, coulomb/cubic metre. This unit is commonly used in the SI unit system. Coulomb Per Cubic Meter has a dimension of $L^{-3}TI$ where $L$ is length, $T$ is time, and $I$ is electric current. This unit is the standard SI unit in this category.",
            "lang": "en"
        }
    ],
